<br>
I'm with you 100% on the multiple pets issue.  That's why the idea of calling for specials sounds pretty good to me.  I can see using one solid, well armored tank type pet and a second with interesting specials.  Send in the tank first, then call for intimidates or blinds as needed.<br>
<br>
It comes very close to doing something I've always wanted them to do, which is add special purpose utility pets.  ATM, everything interesting about a pet merges into the same overall calculus:  how well does it tank.  I wanted them to add pets that had utility functions -- if pet X is out, all your pets heal 25% faster, or pet Y can perform a resource survey equal to a novice artisan's, or something like that.<br>
<br>
This is close -- lets me use pets with various special attacks for utility purposes. I can have a good poisoner without needing to worry about it being able to tank.  Like that idea.<br>
<br>
Time will tell. . .  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> joboosc</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#70DB93>(10/28/03 3:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Irene, your PR boss should give you a bonus</span><hr size=1> Really, how much are you getting paid to post web propaganda? Judging from your IQ-level must not be a high wage.<br>
