<br>
Youre faith in SOE to make all things right is admirable. I used to be like that years ago. I can still remember being one of "those people" that made posts slamming the people that made negative posts against Verant and EQ. "Its a great game!" Id say, "Go ahead and quit! We dont care!" heh heh Oh man..I feel stupid just typing that. Over time though I was beaten into submission with the nerf stick over and over again. It didnt matter if their choice was completely stupid, illogical, and made the game less fun. Wed all suck it up and keep on playing because there was always that little glimmer of hope that kept us going... "someday they will fix it" was the whisper on various boards across the internet. But up until about 4 or 5 months ago, it didnt change. It didnt get better. Infact it got worse. <br>
<br>
The escalation of mudflation had reached all new heights, and the downward spiral of ingame fun had bottomed out. I left a 65 Ogre Warrior in a Planar guild, killing gods, getting massive amounts of "uber lewtz" each and every night. Killing Rallos Zek was quite a thrill to finally do. Getting to do exp grinds in Plane of Fire and Plane of Earth were entertaining... but it just wasnt enough to hold me. It was a job, not a fun game I played to pass the time. It was work. <br>
<br>
Now comes SWG, and my faith in SOE is faltering once again. Jaded I may be. I recall once again standing up to critics who denounced this game. Said that Sony would ruin it like they ruined EQ. They couldnt possibly get it right...etc etc. I replied to them saying that George Lucas and LucasArts would never let SOE warp Star Wars. Was I stupid to believe so easily? Im certianly no purist, like some of the morons on the official boards calling for removal of the CH profession because its not "Star Warsy" ... whatever that means. I play this game to have fun. So far, the ONLY fun I have found is the taming and training of creatures and using them in battle. If anyone comes in and touches that ability, then I get defensive. I dont care about other peoples fun...its their responsibility to find their own fun. If their class is broken, then they should go after the devs to fix it. But what Im seeing, ever so much more in this game than EQ ever was, is alot of nerf crying from people who refuse to understand.<br>
<br>
So yeah... Im negative. 4.5 years of lost faith and cynical expectations have smoothed me over enough that when a dev posts something about how they are going to "change", "adjust", "tweak", or flat out "nerf"...then I tend to expect the worse. SOE doesnt adjust, tweak, or change using a scalpel. They use a big iron wrecking ball, and they swing it around wildly.<br>
<br>
Ask yourself this, Has any dev thought just for an instant "Gee...why are so many people gravitating towards pets in this game? What is the big draw? Why do some players feel compelled to have pets at all times?" If they had asked themselves these questions, do you think they would have come up with the same answers to the problems as they have recently? Does it make sense to adjust one of the very FEW working professions in the game without giving thought to the ones that are completely broken? How can you even expect to balance anything in that manner? Youre balancing a working skill vs broken skills. So now youve broken the working skill and now EVERYONE is broken. How does this fix anything? <br>
<br>
Its like the Commando Syndrome. You have a class that is completely useless. It does nothing of what it is supposed to do. Infact for almost 2 months the class specific weapons didnt even exist for them. The devs proceed to nerf skills and abilities of other classes. Pistoleers, BH, Carbineers, Riflemen... all recieved some sort of decrese in a power or skill before Commandos were actually fixed. Now they fix Commandos and they are where every other combat class used to be. Now people are crying over Commandos doing too much damage. <br>
<br>
When you stand back and look at every combat related profession with an open mind, you can see that they all have their problems. Right down to the so called "overpowered" CH. The poor melees in the game havnt got a chance. The way this game is made really boggles my mind. We need the pets we have now to ever stand a chance of killing any high end content. So what happens after were all nerfed down, and SOE throws in some nasty high end content, or new adventure worlds that make Dathomir look like a Tatooine Newbie Yard? Then what? Have the melees tank? I dont think so. SOE would have to completely restructure their combat system, which would completely destroy the already wierd PvP system they have. <br>
<br>
Eventually someone out there will actually see that its the game that is flawed at its very core and not so much the professions like CH that actually work right. I really dont think its a bad thing for people to call out the devs on this fact. If its looked upon as negative, then so be it. Someone has to do it. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.netset.com/~blazer/sig3.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
